Peru Stocks: Buenaventura, Edegel, Siderperu, Telefonica, Volcan

-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 
2011-04-28T21:10:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-28/peru-stocks-buenaventura-edegel-siderperu-telefonica-volcan.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Peru  trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses
and share prices are as of 4:10 p.m.  New York  time.  The Lima General Index jumped 5.6 percent to 18,971.59, the
biggest gain since May 2009. The MSCI All Peru Capped Index rose
4.8 percent to 2,579.59.  Industrial stocks and utilities surged as an election poll
gave presidential candidate Ollanta Humala a smaller lead than a
previous survey ahead of the June 5 vote, said Leoncio Altamirano, a trader at Lima-based Juan Magot y Asociados SAB.
Humala has pledged higher taxes for mining companies and to
renegotiate free-trade accords with the U.S. and other
countries.  Refineria la Pampilla SA (RELAPAC1 PE), a unit of  Spain ’s
Repsol YPF SA, jumped 10 percent to 1.48 soles, its biggest one-
day gain in 18 months.  Cementos Lima SA (CEMLIMI1)  (CEMLIMC1 PE), the
country’s biggest cement maker, rose 10 percent to 2.50 soles
after reporting first-quarter net income climbed 27 percent.
Edegel SA (EDEGELC1 PE), the Peruvian unit of Spain’s Endesa SA,
gained 9.7 percent to 1.70 soles.  Empresa Siderurgica del Peru
SAA (SIDERC1)  (SIDERC1 PE), a unit of Gerdau SA,  Latin America ’s largest
steelmaker, gained 9.6 percent to 1.26 soles.  Telefonica del
Peru SAA (TELEFBC1)  (TELEFBC1 PE), the local unit of Telefonica SA, climbed
8 percent to 2.70 soles after first-quarter net income rose 30
percent to 201 million soles.  Mining stocks rebounded after metals advanced in New York
and  London .  Alturas Minerals Corp. (ALT)  , a Canadian copper and gold
exploration company, soared 15 percent to 15 cents.  Minsur SA (MINSURI1) 
(MINSURI1 PE), the world’s fourth-largest tin producer, rose 12
percent to 3.43 soles. Volcan Cia Minera SAA (VOLCABC1 PE),
Peru’s largest silver producer, gained 11 percent to 2.95 soles.
Sociedad Minera Cerro Verde SA (CVERDEC1 PE), a unit of
Freeport-McMoRan Copper & Gold Inc., rose 9 percent to $37.60.
Cia. de Minas Buenaventura SAA (BVN PE), the country’s biggest
precious-metals miner which is scheduled to report earnings
today, gained 5.3 percent to $40.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
